-not to be your father.
-Oh.

263
00:12:36.798 --> 00:12:38.049
What's wrong with his father?

264
00:12:38.132 --> 00:12:40.677
You mean
the number one villain in all of Auradon?

265
00:12:41.219 --> 00:12:43.179
At least I'm not Luisa Jr.

266
00:12:43.263 --> 00:12:46.057
Do they feed you more than hay up on
that mountain. Madrigal?

267
00:12:46.140 --> 00:12:48.643
How about you
just keep it moving. huh. Hatter?

268
00:12:48.726 --> 00:12:50.937
I'm sure the Hat Trix
need help lurking somewhere.

269
00:12:51.020 --> 00:12:52.272
Get out of here.

270
00:12:52.355 --> 00:12:54.195
I know
you're not dissing my crew.

271
00:12:54.232 --> 00:12:57.735
We may be back at school.
but you're not gonna like the lesson

272
00:12:57.819 --> 00:12:59.320
the Smees and I will teach you.

273
00:12:59.404 --> 00:13:00.571
Yeah!

274
00:13:00.655 --> 00:13:04.200
Allow me. Hazel.
May I suggest a Facilier family specialty?

275
00:13:04.284 --> 00:13:06.494
How original. A pirate itching to fight.

276
00:13:08.454 --> 00:13:09.706
What is that?

277
00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:19.841
What is it. Red?

278
00:13:21.050 --> 00:13:24.304
Maddox Hatter
has captured the Queen. Come quickly!

279
00:13:25.138 --> 00:13:26.139
No!

280
00:13:26.222 --> 00:13:27.724
Maddox?

281
00:13:27.807 --> 00:13:29.642
Thank you. Ooh!

282
00:13:29.726 --> 00:13:31.144
Stop messing around. Felix.

283
00:13:31.227 --> 00:13:33.187
-What? What?
-It's not funny.

284
00:13:36.065 --> 00:13:37.650
You can give it back now.

285
00:13:43.656 --> 00:13:45.158
Oh. my hearts!

286
00:13:45.241 --> 00:13:46.701
You gotta stop doing that.

287
00:13:46.784 --> 00:13:48.995
-Oh. my hearts!
-Hey. hey. calm down.

288
00:13:49.078 --> 00:13:51.581
-Don't freak out.
-Mom's been captured!

289
00:13:52.957 --> 00:13:54.709
Whoa. whoa. whoa!

290
00:13:55.251 --> 00:13:57.754
-Now. princes a.
-Great.

291
00:13:57.837 --> 00:13:59.047
Let's get you up.

292
00:13:59.130 --> 00:14:00.882
What the fluff!

293
00:14:00.965 --> 00:14:02.717
Did my pumpkins go rogue again?

294
00:14:02.800 --> 00:14:04.135
Let's get out of here. Come on.

295
00:14:04.635 --> 00:14:05.720
Is that a no?

296
00:14:06.804 --> 00:14:08.556
We gotta get back to Wonderland now.

297
00:14:08.639 --> 00:14:10.725
Okay. We should find my mom.
She'll help us.

298
00:14:10.808 --> 00:14:12.018
Absolutely not.

299
00:14:12.101 --> 00:14:13.144
Go to Wonderland?

300
00:14:13.227 --> 00:14:14.562
Without Auradon guards?

301
00:14:14.645 --> 00:14:16.397
Without the other kingdoms' help?

302
00:14:16.481 --> 00:14:19.150
There are rules. Chloe.
Protocols to follow.

303
00:14:19.233 --> 00:14:21.611
But when it's important.
rules don't matter.

304
00:14:21.694 --> 00:14:24.072
We just have to get in there
and get our hands dirty.

305
00:14:24.155 --> 00:14:25.406
Right. Mom?

306
00:14:25.948 --> 00:14:28.034
Girls.
you can't just bibbidi-bop yourselves

307
00:14:28.117 --> 00:14:29.744
into a dangerous villain's hands.

308
00:14:29.827 --> 00:14:31.245
No. ma'ams.

309
00:14:31.329 --> 00:14:33.706
Maddox is not to be trifled with.

310
00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:37.502
He's terrorized the kingdoms for years
with his deranged inventions.

311
00:14:37.585 --> 00:14:40.379
Your mother had him banished
to the Isle of the Lost.

312
00:14:40.463 --> 00:14:41.714
He's a madman.

313
00:14:41.798 --> 00:14:42.882
In your time.

314
00:14:44.300 --> 00:14:47.345
Now. I spoke with Uma.
and she's calling the Auradon Council.

315
00:14:47.428 --> 00:14:50.389
and they're coming up with
a carefully thought out rescue plan

316
00:14:50.473 --> 00:14:52.225
that leaves nothing to chance.

317
00:14:52.308 --> 00:14:54.560
A plan? That's it?

318
00:14:54.644 --> 00:14:56.145
Yes.

319
00:14:56.229 --> 00:14:58.231
What happens to my mom in the meantime?

320
00:14:58.314 --> 00:14:59.524
We just leave her there?

321
00:14:59.607 --> 00:15:00.775
Mom. come on.

322
00:15:00.858 --> 00:15:04.195
We don't break rules. Chloe.
even for a good cause.

323
00:15:04.278 --> 00:15:05.696
But you don't really believe that.

324
00:15:05.780 --> 00:15:06.948
She's your best friend.

325
00:15:07.031 --> 00:15:09.492
You'll stay here and let us handle this.

326
00:15:09.575 --> 00:15:10.576
Promise me.

327
00:15:10.660 --> 00:15:12.995
People look to us
to do what's right. Chloe.

328
00:15:13.079 --> 00:15:15.957
You're a Charming.
You need to act accordingly.

329
00:15:16.749 --> 00:15:18.626
What?

330
00:15:18.709 --> 00:15:19.794
What was he thinking?

331
00:15:19.877 --> 00:15:20.962
Kidnapping the Queen?

332
00:15:21.045 --> 00:15:23.089
Well. at least you're here
and he's in Wonderland.

333
00:15:23.172 --> 00:15:25.424
-No one can blame you.
-Except they do.

334
00:15:25.967 --> 00:15:27.176
I'm tied to him.

335
00:15:27.260 --> 00:15:28.553
It doesn't matter where I am.

336
00:15:28.636 --> 00:15:30.763
I wish there was a way
I could change that.

337
00:15:30.847 --> 00:15:33.432
Okay. so stop complaining
and do something about it.

338
00:15:34.559 --> 00:15:35.643
You're right.

339
00:15:36.185 --> 00:15:37.478
You're so right.

340
00:15:37.562 --> 00:15:38.604
Of course I'm right.

341
00:15:38.688 --> 00:15:40.231
Okay. Get Felix and the Smees.

342
00:15:40.314 --> 00:15:41.634
Meet me at the Rabbit Hole. Yeah?

343
00:15:41.691 --> 00:15:42.733
Wait. What?

344
00:15:42.817 --> 00:15:44.527
No. I didn't mean right now!

345
00:15:45.903 --> 00:15:47.572
We haven't even had lunch yet.

346
00:15:52.493 --> 00:15:54.245
Red. wait up.

347
00:15:54.954 --> 00:15:56.205
Disobeying your mom?

348
00:15:56.289 --> 00:15:58.082
I guess I really have corrupted you.

349
00:15:58.166 --> 00:16:00.042
Okay. don't give yourself too much credit.

350
00:16:00.126 --> 00:16:02.606
I mean. she was the one
who taught me that a lie to save a life

351
00:16:02.670 --> 00:16:05.548
was a good trade. even if
she doesn't remember it.

352
00:16:05.631 --> 00:16:08.801
What your mom said in there
about Maddox on the isle. that's us.

353
00:16:08.885 --> 00:16:10.761
Chloe. we did that.

354
00:16:13.264 --> 00:16:16.392
I finally got the mom I always wanted.
and now we put her in danger.

355
00:16:17.268 --> 00:16:18.728
It's gonna be okay.

356
00:16:18.811 --> 00:16:20.271
We'll figure it out together.

357
00:16:21.189 --> 00:16:22.690
I hope your plan includes us...

358
00:16:22.773 --> 00:16:24.525
because we're coming
with you to Wonderland.

359
00:16:24.609 --> 00:16:25.735
Yeah. I don't think so.

360
00:16:25.818 --> 00:16:27.778
Our interests don't exactly align.

361
00:16:27.862 --> 00:16:28.863
Come on. Red.

362
00:16:28.946 --> 00:16:32.366
You need someone that knows how to
beat my father at his own game.

363
00:16:32.450 --> 00:16:33.492
And I can help with that.

364
00:16:33.576 --> 00:16:35.411
You'd sell out your dad?

365
00:16:35.494 --> 00:16:36.495
It's not so easy.

366
00:16:37.205 --> 00:16:38.873
Well. good news. princess.

367
00:16:38.956 --> 00:16:40.666
Not much of my life has been easy.

368
00:16:41.417 --> 00:16:43.461
And I have my dad to thank for that.

369
00:16:43.544 --> 00:16:45.296
But I'm not him.

370
00:16:46.172 --> 00:16:47.423
And I never want to be.

371
00:16:47.965 --> 00:16:49.383
Wait for Pink. too.

372
00:16:51.552 --> 00:16:53.346
Not to fear. help is here.

373
00:16:53.429 --> 00:16:55.056
Two merry men reporting for duty.

374
00:16:55.139 --> 00:16:56.140
I brought snacks.

375
00:16:56.224 --> 00:16:57.725
Though apparently not enough.

376
00:16:57.808 --> 00:16:58.976
What are they doing here?

377
00:16:59.060 --> 00:17:00.519
What are they doing here?

378
00:17:00.603 --> 00:17:01.604
This is going well.

379
00:17:04.190 --> 00:17:05.858
What kind of snacks did you bring?

380
00:17:06.859 --> 00:17:07.860
What?

381
00:17:07.944 --> 00:17:10.047
I have to feed the Smees every two hours.

382
00:17:10.071 --> 00:17:11.155
Fine.

383
00:17:11.239 --> 00:17:12.615
Come on.

384
00:17:21.415 --> 00:17:23.251
-Jump?
-Yep.

385
00:17:23.334 --> 00:17:24.669
Down the hatch.

386
00:17:24.752 --> 00:17:27.338
Into the endless void
where we can't even see the bottom?

387
00:17:27.880 --> 00:17:28.923
Cool.

388
00:17:29.507 --> 00:17:30.675
Scared?

389
00:17:30.758 --> 00:17:31.801
No.

390
00:17:31.884 --> 00:17:33.844
-Let's do it.
-Yeah.

391
00:17:40.268 --> 00:17:41.519
It's your show. Princess.

392
00:17:42.353 --> 00:17:44.397
Will everyone just cool it with that?

393
00:17:44.480 --> 00:17:45.690
It's not Princess.

394
00:17:45.773 --> 00:17:47.942
It's just... Red.

395
00:17:52.071 --> 00:17:53.281
Here we go.

396
00:17:58.869 --> 00:18:00.246
Whoa!

397
00:18:00.329 --> 00:18:01.372
Oh. my...

398
00:18:03.833 --> 00:18:04.917
Whoo.

399
00:18:07.295 --> 00:18:10.006
-One. two. Smee!
-One. two. Smee!

400
00:18:19.557 --> 00:18:20.683
Whoo!

401
00:18:22.935 --> 00:18:24.645
Smees. cut it out!

402
00:18:35.531 --> 00:18:37.074
Red. what is this?

403
00:18:37.158 --> 00:18:38.492
I don't know.

404
00:18:53.341 --> 00:18:56.010
I just love when
butterflies greet us!

405
00:18:56.093 --> 00:18:57.303
Look!

406
00:18:59.889 --> 00:19:02.099
-Hi. Margaret.
-Oh. hello. Pink.

407
00:19:02.183 --> 00:19:04.393
-Hi. Tabitha!
-Hi. Pink!

408
00:19:05.686 --> 00:19:08.397
I don't know why you'd
ever want to leave a place so wonderful.

409
00:19:08.481 --> 00:19:11.859
This isn't the Wonderland I grew up with.

410
00:19:13.194 --> 00:19:14.195
Whoa!

411
00:19:14.779 --> 00:19:17.406
So where is this palace of yours?
I don't see it.

412
00:19:17.490 --> 00:19:18.616
No!

413
00:19:27.958 --> 00:19:30.336
Come on. guys.
We've got a long journey ahead.

414
00:19:32.296 --> 00:19:33.547
Are you sure about this?

415
00:19:33.631 --> 00:19:35.174
Think we can trust this redhead?

416
00:19:35.257 --> 00:19:36.300
Of course not.

417
00:19:36.384 --> 00:19:38.386
But this is the only way to stop my dad.

418
00:19:43.766 --> 00:19:45.810
My cards!

419
00:19:48.646 --> 00:19:51.399
Oh. no. Oh. no.

420
00:20:02.993 --> 00:20:04.120
Hatter!

421
00:20:05.121 --> 00:20:07.039
This way is quickest to the palace.

422
00:20:07.123 --> 00:20:08.684
It's also the prettiest.

423
00:20:08.708 --> 00:20:10.251
-Wow!
-It's so colorful!

424
00:20:10.334 --> 00:20:11.919
-Smees!
-As you enter.

425
00:20:12.002 --> 00:20:15.089
Wonderland's croquet gardens.
please pay special attention

426
00:20:15.172 --> 00:20:17.466
to all the magical
flora and fauna. And Smees.

427
00:20:17.550 --> 00:20:19.468
don't eat any of our special friends...

428
00:20:19.969 --> 00:20:21.470
You're it!

429
00:20:22.054 --> 00:20:25.850
Like our living mushrooms.
or our beautiful flamingos.

430
00:20:25.933 --> 00:20:27.268
Oh. they're very cuddly!

431
00:20:28.978 --> 00:20:30.896
Wow. Look at Felix.

432
00:20:30.980 --> 00:20:34.316
Who knew the Faciliers
were such bird lovers?

433
00:20:37.236 --> 00:20:40.364
Red. look.
the pink spotted tickler rose. Here.

434
00:20:40.948 --> 00:20:42.032
For me?

435
00:20:42.116 --> 00:20:43.451
They're your favorite.

436
00:20:47.246 --> 00:20:50.291
Okay. everyone. we should
keep moving through Tulgey Woods.

437
00:20:50.374 --> 00:20:52.835
We follow that path
straight to the castle.

438
00:20:55.588 --> 00:20:59.633
Maddox. come here quickly.

439
00:20:59.717 --> 00:21:00.968
Maddox!

440
00:21:01.886 --> 00:21:03.304
Look what the dodos found.

441
00:21:03.387 --> 00:21:05.347
Intruders.

442
00:21:05.431 --> 00:21:06.932
And your son.

443
00:21:07.808 --> 00:21:09.518
Oh. Max!

444
00:21:10.436 --> 00:21:12.229
How could you betray me?

445
00:21:12.855 --> 00:21:16.400
Uh. guys... what's happening?

446
00:21:16.484 --> 00:21:18.527
-Smees.
-Stay close.

447
00:21:19.195 --> 00:21:20.738
Max. what is this?

448
00:21:20.821 --> 00:21:22.198
It's my dad.

449
00:21:22.698 --> 00:21:23.949
He knows we're here.

450
00:21:27.286 --> 00:21:28.788
Well. well...

451
00:21:29.580 --> 00:21:31.707
Let the games begin.

452
00:21:31.791 --> 00:21:35.586
♪ Now look what the cat dragged in
to come and visit ♪

453
00:21:35.669 --> 00:21:37.421
♪ Pathetic Exquisite ♪

454
00:21:37.505 --> 00:21:39.298
♪ Now whose unbirthday is it? ♪

455
00:21:39.381 --> 00:21:41.133
♪ Got some tricks up my sleeve ♪

456
00:21:41.217 --> 00:21:42.927
♪ And a watch on my mind ♪

457
00:21:43.010 --> 00:21:45.137
♪ And once I get what I want ♪

458
00:21:45.221 --> 00:21:47.306
♪ All the power is mine Ha! ♪

459
00:21:47.389 --> 00:21:49.475
♪ Down is up. up is down ♪

460
00:21:49.558 --> 00:21:51.393
♪ Trade my top hat for a crown ♪

461
00:21:51.477 --> 00:21:53.103
♪ Down is up. up is down ♪

462
00:21:53.813 --> 00:21:55.564
♪ Welcome to my Wonderland ♪

463
00:21:55.648 --> 00:21:56.649
Run!

464
00:21:56.732 --> 00:21:58.400
♪ To my Wonderland ♪

465
00:21:58.484 --> 00:22:00.486
♪ Truth or dare
Are you scared? ♪

466
00:22:00.569 --> 00:22:01.695
♪ That's too bad ♪

467
00:22:01.779 --> 00:22:03.113
♪ Welcome to my Wonderland ♪

468
00:22:03.864 --> 00:22:06.492
♪ It's better than I planned ♪

469
00:22:06.575 --> 00:22:10.538
♪ What a time
Most fun I've ever had ♪

470
00:22:10.621 --> 00:22:12.957
♪ I've never been so happy being mad ♪

471
00:22:13.791 --> 00:22:15.042
Smees!

472
00:22:19.171 --> 00:22:20.631
You just had to kiss it?

473
00:22:24.510 --> 00:22:26.512
♪ My father is twisted ♪

474
00:22:26.595 --> 00:22:28.305
♪ Well. you are related ♪

475
00:22:28.389 --> 00:22:30.266
♪ Cold hearted. sadistic ♪

476
00:22:30.349 --> 00:22:32.184
♪ Warm hugs are overrated ♪

477
00:22:32.268 --> 00:22:33.936
♪ This whole destructive spree ♪

478
00:22:34.019 --> 00:22:35.938
♪ Will fall right back on me ♪

479
00:22:36.021 --> 00:22:39.650
♪ I've had enough
This time I'm finally breaking free ♪

480
00:22:39.733 --> 00:22:41.527
♪ Down is up. up is down ♪

481
00:22:41.610 --> 00:22:43.737
♪ Turn the tables on him now ♪

482
00:22:43.821 --> 00:22:45.573
-Go!
-♪ Down is up. up is down ♪

483
00:22:46.115 --> 00:22:48.492
-♪ Welcome to my Wonderland ♪
-Go. go. go!

484
00:22:48.576 --> 00:22:50.744
♪ To my Wonderland ♪

485
00:22:50.828 --> 00:22:52.580
♪ Truth or dare
Are you scared? ♪

486
00:22:52.663 --> 00:22:53.914
♪ That's too bad ♪

487
00:22:53.998 --> 00:22:56.083
♪ Welcome to my Wonderland ♪

488
00:22:56.166 --> 00:22:58.377
♪ It's better than I planned ♪

489
00:22:58.460 --> 00:23:02.131
♪ What a time
Most fun I've ever had ♪

490
00:23:02.756 --> 00:23:05.593
♪ I've never been so happy being mad ♪

491
00:23:11.348 --> 00:23:12.641
Lights out.

492
00:23:17.187 --> 00:23:18.898
-Stop! Wait!
-Stop! Wait!

493
00:23:18.981 --> 00:23:20.858
♪ Don't make them pay for my mistake ♪

494
00:23:20.941 --> 00:23:24.904
♪ I should never have
let you return back home ♪

495
00:23:24.987 --> 00:23:29.116
♪ This battle's between us and us alone ♪

496
00:23:29.199 --> 00:23:32.703
♪ So just let them go ♪

497
00:23:33.412 --> 00:23:34.830
Are you guys okay?

498
00:23:34.914 --> 00:23:35.915
No.

499
00:23:35.998 --> 00:23:37.416
♪ I spent too many years ♪

500
00:23:37.499 --> 00:23:39.293
♪ On that wretched isle ♪

501
00:23:39.376 --> 00:23:41.170
♪ Cast aside. doing time ♪

502
00:23:41.253 --> 00:23:42.963
♪ Pushed me over the edge ♪

503
00:23:43.047 --> 00:23:46.717
♪ But the way you beg and plead
is bringing back my smile ♪

504
00:23:46.800 --> 00:23:51.180
♪ Understand Wonderland's
gonna feel my revenge ♪

505
00:23:51.263 --> 00:23:53.015
-♪ You're heartless ♪
-♪ You mean it? ♪

506
00:23:53.098 --> 00:23:54.099
You monster!

507
00:23:54.183 --> 00:23:55.184
Believe it.

508
00:23:55.267 --> 00:23:57.227
You'll never get away with this!

509
00:23:57.311 --> 00:23:59.772
♪ I already have ♪

510
00:23:59.855 --> 00:24:01.982
♪ Welcome to my Wonderland ♪

511
00:24:02.066 --> 00:24:04.276
♪ To my Wonderland ♪

512
00:24:04.360 --> 00:24:06.445
♪ Truth or dare
Are you scared? ♪

513
00:24:06.528 --> 00:24:07.571
♪ That's too bad ♪

514
00:24:07.655 --> 00:24:09.698
♪ Welcome to my Wonderland ♪

515
00:24:09.782 --> 00:24:11.617
♪ It's better than I planned ♪

516
00:24:12.159 --> 00:24:16.413
♪ What a time
Most fun I've ever had ♪

517
00:24:16.497 --> 00:24:18.540
♪ I've never been so happy being ♪

518
00:24:18.624 --> 00:24:20.459
♪ Criminal beyond all reason ♪

519
00:24:20.542 --> 00:24:22.544
♪ Never been so happy being ♪

520
00:24:22.628 --> 00:24:24.046
-Wait!
-♪ Mad! ♪

521
00:24:26.465 --> 00:24:29.468
You're getting fingerprints on my crystal!

522
00:24:29.551 --> 00:24:31.637
I will find your vault.

523
00:24:32.638 --> 00:24:36.600
How long your rescuers suffer until I do
is up to you.

524
00:24:36.684 --> 00:24:39.895
You underestimate my girls.

525
00:24:39.979 --> 00:24:41.647
You underestimate...

526
00:24:42.815 --> 00:24:43.857
me.

527
00:24:56.036 --> 00:24:57.371
And stay out.

528
00:24:57.454 --> 00:24:59.164
What was that?

529
00:24:59.248 --> 00:25:01.250
Well. I'm partial to "gracias."

530
00:25:01.333 --> 00:25:03.293
but. uh. "thank you" also works.

531
00:25:04.086 --> 00:25:06.630
you know. for saving you.

532
00:25:06.714 --> 00:25:09.258
Does it look like we're saved?

533
00:25:10.426 --> 00:25:12.928
Wait. where is everybody?

534
00:25:13.929 --> 00:25:19.518
Probably behind door number one.
two or... seven ninety-four.

535
00:25:21.061 --> 00:25:22.688
But. hey. this is your backyard. right?

536
00:25:22.771 --> 00:25:25.107
So. uh. which one do we start with?

537
00:25:26.442 --> 00:25:27.860
I wish I knew.

538
00:25:27.943 --> 00:25:29.194
What was that?

539
00:25:29.278 --> 00:25:30.696
Let's go with this one.

540
00:25:31.655 --> 00:25:33.907
Uh. this one's the one.

541
00:25:33.991 --> 00:25:35.576
-Yeah.
-Lead the way.

542
00:25:35.659 --> 00:25:36.994
I'm sure everybody's fine.

543
00:25:40.914 --> 00:25:42.458
Whoa!

544
00:25:42.541 --> 00:25:43.667
Get off me!

545
00:25:44.251 --> 00:25:46.545
Whoa!

546
00:25:47.337 --> 00:25:48.839
Looks like a fun guy.

547
00:25:52.968 --> 00:25:54.887
-No luck?
-Let's keep going.

548
00:25:56.680 --> 00:25:58.682
They've got to be around here somewhere.

549
00:26:00.350 --> 00:26:01.977
Ugh! What?

550
00:26:03.645 --> 00:26:05.647
Are you sure you're going the right way?

551
00:26:05.731 --> 00:26:07.858
I'm walking this way. aren't I?

552
00:26:07.941 --> 00:26:11.945
How does one get lost
in their own kingdom. exactly?

553
00:26:13.155 --> 00:26:14.490
Fine.

554
00:26:15.199 --> 00:26:16.700
You got me. Okay?

555
00:26:16.784 --> 00:26:18.035
I don't like bows.

556
00:26:18.118 --> 00:26:19.536
I prefer swords to sparkles.

557
00:26:19.620 --> 00:26:21.747
And this isn't my backyard.

558
00:26:21.830 --> 00:26:22.956
-I didn't...
-You try being

559
00:26:23.040 --> 00:26:25.417
shut off from the world your whole life.

560
00:26:25.501 --> 00:26:28.504
and the minute you get
a whiff of fresh air. you screw it up.

561
00:26:28.587 --> 00:26:31.882
Not just for yourself.
but for everyone you've ever cared about.

562
00:26:35.135 --> 00:26:37.096
-I didn't mean it like that.
-It's okay.

563
00:26:37.179 --> 00:26:38.263
I get it.

564
00:26:40.057 --> 00:26:43.060
Trust me. I...
I know a thing or two about family legacy.

565
00:26:44.520 --> 00:26:48.607
a blessing and a curse
all wrapped up together.

566
00:26:48.690 --> 00:26:50.025
I'm Louisa Madrigal's son.

567
00:26:50.109 --> 00:26:52.444
I'm supposed to be strong. no matter what.

568
00:26:53.612 --> 00:26:55.447
Good thing I can. uh. shoulder it.

569
00:26:58.200 --> 00:27:00.410
You gotta chill with all that.

570
00:27:00.494 --> 00:27:01.995
It's too much.

571
00:27:02.079 --> 00:27:05.332
Sorry. It's kind of what people expect.

572
00:27:05.874 --> 00:27:07.835
What they want from me.

573
00:27:07.918 --> 00:27:09.920
All they seem to want from me.

574
00:27:11.755 --> 00:27:12.965
Okay. but...

575
00:27:13.757 --> 00:27:15.175
What do you want for you?

576
00:27:18.846 --> 00:27:21.723
I don't think anyone's
ever asked me that before.

577
00:27:26.895 --> 00:27:30.148
You know. now. I think
it's the part where you

578
00:27:31.650 --> 00:27:33.986
apologize for dragging me
out of a doorway.

579
00:27:34.069 --> 00:27:35.696
What?

580
00:27:35.779 --> 00:27:38.115
-But I saved you.
-I can't with you.

581
00:27:38.824 --> 00:27:41.243
Is there an update
from Uma or the council?

582
00:27:41.326 --> 00:27:44.538
Yes.
News from Fairy Godmother. Your Majesty.

583
00:27:47.499 --> 00:27:50.711
The children have
gone to Wonderland... on their own?

584
00:27:50.794 --> 00:27:53.714
Now they'll have to face Maddox alone.

585
00:27:54.715 --> 00:27:56.466
Chloe. what have you done?

586
00:28:02.389 --> 00:28:03.640
Smee!

587
00:28:06.685 --> 00:28:07.895
Ha!

588
00:28:08.604 --> 00:28:10.689
See? Not lost after all.

589
00:28:11.899 --> 00:28:13.400
Smee!

590
00:28:14.067 --> 00:28:16.862
Red! I was so worried!

591
00:28:17.362 --> 00:28:19.197
You found it! Thank you!

592
00:28:19.281 --> 00:28:20.574
Oh. I missed you. shoe.

593
00:28:20.657 --> 00:28:21.867
Guys. Red found my shoe!

594
00:28:21.950 --> 00:28:23.577
She is a ridiculous person.

595
00:28:23.660 --> 00:28:25.162
Well. we've got a bigger problem.

596
00:28:26.330 --> 00:28:30.292
Whoa! Look. I'm not a fan
of Hazel's either. but let's pull it back.

597
00:28:30.375 --> 00:28:32.252
No. it's not that. It's that.

598
00:28:32.878 --> 00:28:34.546
I saw one in the croquet garden.

599
00:28:34.630 --> 00:28:36.506
It must be a spy for Maddox.

600
00:28:36.590 --> 00:28:39.593
-So that's how he discovered us?
-Exactly.

601
00:28:39.676 --> 00:28:41.845
But listen. if we get the dodo down.

602
00:28:41.929 --> 00:28:44.473
maybe I can pry it open and rewire it.

603
00:28:44.556 --> 00:28:46.224
and then it could spy for us

604
00:28:46.308 --> 00:28:47.976
so we can stay one step ahead of Maddox

605
00:28:48.060 --> 00:28:50.062
and get
to the palace quicker to save your mom.

606
00:28:50.145 --> 00:28:51.438
We should tell Max.

607
00:28:51.521 --> 00:28:52.773
He might know more about them.

608
00:28:52.856 --> 00:28:54.608
But. Red. listen.

609
00:28:54.691 --> 00:28:56.860
-You tricked us.
-I was trying to help.

610
00:28:56.944 --> 00:28:59.071
You like to box?
'Cause I got a killer right hook.

611
00:28:59.154 --> 00:29:01.949
Even you can't think it's a coincidence
he led us to that madhouse.

612
00:29:02.032 --> 00:29:06.036
Guys. before someone gets a nose ring
they didn't consent to. look.

613
00:29:07.120 --> 00:29:08.413
Is it one of your dad's?

614
00:29:09.331 --> 00:29:11.625
Looks like it.
And they'll have a direct line to him.

615
00:29:11.708 --> 00:29:13.877
-We gotta destroy it.
-Or we can try to use it.

616
00:29:13.961 --> 00:29:15.087
No. he's right.

617
00:29:15.170 --> 00:29:16.755
-It's too risky to mess with.
-But...

618
00:29:16.838 --> 00:29:18.715
-I'm on it. Red.
-Wait. Luis.

619
00:29:18.799 --> 00:29:20.926
I got it.

620
00:29:22.010 --> 00:29:24.054
Get a clue you're extinct.

621
00:29:25.472 --> 00:29:28.350
Do you have a brain.
or are you just one big bicep?

622
00:29:29.559 --> 00:29:30.852
Smees. get to climbing.

623
00:29:30.936 --> 00:29:32.020
Hey. put your hands up.

624
00:29:32.104 --> 00:29:33.665
-Come on. make it good. make it good.
-Here I come.

625
00:29:33.689 --> 00:29:35.357
Not each other!

626
00:29:35.440 --> 00:29:37.859
-The tree!
-Maybe we can lure it with treats.

627
00:29:37.943 --> 00:29:39.403
It's a mechanical bird.

628
00:29:39.486 --> 00:29:41.863
Yeah. but it's vanilla.
Everyone loves vanilla.

629
00:29:41.947 --> 00:29:45.200
No. I think if we just think enough...

630
00:29:45.283 --> 00:29:46.743
Yeah.

631
00:29:46.827 --> 00:29:48.704
I think it's calling for more dodos.

632
00:29:48.787 --> 00:29:49.997
Guys. we should keep moving.

633
00:29:50.080 --> 00:29:51.307
Let's cover our tracks. Come on.

634
00:29:54.835 --> 00:29:55.919
Are you coming?

635
00:29:58.088 --> 00:29:59.297
Yeah. coming.

636
00:29:59.965 --> 00:30:01.800
Wait. Where's Robbie?

637
00:30:01.883 --> 00:30:02.926
I thought he was with you.

638
00:30:03.010 --> 00:30:04.720
And Felix. I thought he was with you.

639
00:30:10.892 --> 00:30:13.770
I hate this ride!

640
00:30:14.688 --> 00:30:15.897
Eh.

641
00:30:20.694 --> 00:30:23.572
These kids
are more resilient than I thought.

642
00:30:23.655 --> 00:30:26.616
Chessy.
you cannot let them reach the palace.

643
00:30:26.700 --> 00:30:30.537
I'm on it. This is something
I can really dig my claws into.

644
00:30:33.040 --> 00:30:34.958
Madam. it's too dangerous.

645
00:30:35.042 --> 00:30:37.044
I haven't used it in years.

646
00:30:37.127 --> 00:30:39.755
but it leads directly
to Bridget's throne room.

647
00:30:39.838 --> 00:30:42.174
Your Majesty doesn't know
what waits for her in there.

648
00:30:42.257 --> 00:30:45.218
The Council is taking too long
and Chloe's in real danger.

649
00:30:45.302 --> 00:30:47.679
Find the king and send word
to Fairy Godmother.

650
00:30:48.972 --> 00:30:50.932
It's time to be brave like my daughter.

651
00:30:56.980 --> 00:30:58.523
Oh. my. Hello?

652
00:31:02.277 --> 00:31:03.445
Come on. old friend.

653
00:31:05.989 --> 00:31:06.990
I'm coming. Chloe.

654
00:31:09.034 --> 00:31:10.118
But not like this.

655
00:31:16.792 --> 00:31:18.335
-Bridget!
-Ella?

656
00:31:18.418 --> 00:31:19.419
Ella!

657
00:31:22.089 --> 00:31:23.590
Whoo! That felt good.

658
00:31:25.550 --> 00:31:28.261
Say what you will about
your stepmother's parenting.

659
00:31:28.345 --> 00:31:30.847
but you can sure
handle yourself with a broom.

660
00:31:30.931 --> 00:31:32.474
-Are you hurt?
-Oh!

661
00:31:32.557 --> 00:31:33.725
Are you all right?

662
00:31:34.392 --> 00:31:35.644
Are you wearing trousers?

663
00:31:36.728 --> 00:31:37.813
Okay. you're fine.

664
00:31:37.896 --> 00:31:40.023
Bridget. the girls are here in Wonderland.

665
00:31:40.107 --> 00:31:41.233
They came to rescue you.

666
00:31:41.316 --> 00:31:42.776
We have to get them to safety.

667
00:31:42.859 --> 00:31:45.779
I know. but he
bewitched my throne room. I'm locked in.

668
00:31:45.862 --> 00:31:48.156
I wasn't expecting visitors.

669
00:31:48.240 --> 00:31:50.534
I didn't get your RSVP.

670
00:31:50.617 --> 00:31:51.618
Maddox.

671
00:31:52.494 --> 00:31:53.703
Cinderella.

672
00:31:53.787 --> 00:31:56.373
-She went in alone?
-I couldn't convince her to wait.

673
00:31:58.166 --> 00:31:59.793
-Now it's a party.
-Cinderella!

674
00:32:03.004 --> 00:32:05.799
So. got a Plan B.
or an extra pair of trousers?

675
00:32:06.800 --> 00:32:08.301
These are the only ones I own.

676
00:32:09.636 --> 00:32:11.847
Time to tighten up security here.

677
00:32:12.472 --> 00:32:16.268
No one's coming to save you now.

678
00:32:17.853 --> 00:32:19.980
We shouldn't be
out here in the dark.

679
00:32:20.063 --> 00:32:21.833
We won't be able to see
if my dad's set another trap.

680
00:32:21.857 --> 00:32:23.457
I'm not taking your advice again.

681
00:32:23.483 --> 00:32:26.778
Guys. enough.
He's right. Max threw us way off course.

682
00:32:30.824 --> 00:32:33.118
We need to find a place
to hide out till morning.

683
00:32:33.201 --> 00:32:34.828
There's a Lumoria Tree. Red.

684
00:32:34.911 --> 00:32:36.705
It'll keep us safe
from Maddox for the night.

685
00:32:42.294 --> 00:32:44.588
Okay. Anyone want tea?

686
00:32:44.671 --> 00:32:47.924
You're like a little
Wonderland survivalist. aren't ya?

687
00:32:51.970 --> 00:32:53.430
I was thinking.

688
00:32:53.513 --> 00:32:55.515
How about you. me. and the other HKs

689
00:32:55.599 --> 00:32:57.475
take the point heading
to the Palace tomorrow?

690
00:32:58.268 --> 00:32:59.603
I don't trust these VKs.

691
00:32:59.686 --> 00:33:01.646
What are they really
bringing to the table?

692
00:33:01.730 --> 00:33:05.442
Ugh. these hero types
think they own the world.

693
00:33:05.525 --> 00:33:07.819
Time to show 'em VKs can run it.

694
00:33:07.903 --> 00:33:09.696
Not so fast. Senor Hero.

695
00:33:10.614 --> 00:33:14.326
You're gonna need a lot more than good
hair and a nice smile to get this done.

696
00:33:14.409 --> 00:33:17.078
You're way more than good hair.

697
00:33:17.162 --> 00:33:19.915
And what does
Hazel Hook know about saving the day?

698
00:33:19.998 --> 00:33:22.292
So why don't you leave
the real work to us villains?

699
00:33:22.375 --> 00:33:25.795
A Madrigal never
backs down from a challenge.

700
00:33:25.879 --> 00:33:27.964
Go comb your hair. pretty boy.

701
00:33:28.048 --> 00:33:29.466
What are you gonna do? Smile at us?

702
00:33:29.549 --> 00:33:32.719
All right. I've been hearing
a lot of talk from the both of you.

703
00:33:32.802 --> 00:33:35.972
but who's really
got what it takes to defeat Maddox? Hmm?

704
00:33:38.266 --> 00:33:40.810
You got this.

705
00:33:42.646 --> 00:33:44.356
♪ Listen up ♪

706
00:33:44.439 --> 00:33:45.732
♪ I don't mean to flex ♪

707
00:33:45.815 --> 00:33:47.359
♪ But let's just be honest ♪

708
00:33:47.442 --> 00:33:48.944
♪ Of everyone you met ♪

709
00:33:49.027 --> 00:33:50.612
♪ I'm undoubtedly the strongest ♪

710
00:33:50.695 --> 00:33:53.990
♪ I got big villain energy
Been scamming since the cradle ♪

711
00:33:54.074 --> 00:33:57.661
♪ From walking planks
to putting chewing gum under your table ♪

712
00:33:58.370 --> 00:34:01.414
♪ The monsters that I fought
are more than just a lot ♪

713
00:34:01.498 --> 00:34:05.252
♪ Once had to put a dragon in a headlock ♪

714
00:34:05.335 --> 00:34:06.586
♪ A pirate in my bones ♪

715
00:34:06.670 --> 00:34:08.255
♪ This hook is solid gold ♪

716
00:34:08.338 --> 00:34:09.881
♪ Believe what you've been told ♪

717
00:34:09.965 --> 00:34:12.008
♪ Did you hear about her? ♪

718
00:34:12.092 --> 00:34:13.551
-♪ Well. she's a prankster ♪
-Aw!

719
00:34:13.635 --> 00:34:15.428
-♪ She's a gangster ♪
-That's so sweet.

720
00:34:15.512 --> 00:34:16.596
♪ She's a boss ♪

721
00:34:16.680 --> 00:34:19.015
-♪ Did you hear about him? ♪
-That's me.

722
00:34:19.099 --> 00:34:20.267
♪ He's the greatest ♪

723
00:34:20.350 --> 00:34:21.768
♪ Not hard to say this ♪

724
00:34:21.851 --> 00:34:23.270
'Cause I'm a fan.

725
00:34:23.353 --> 00:34:25.563
♪ Did you hear about her? ♪

726
00:34:25.647 --> 00:34:27.107
♪ I killed a Kraken ♪

727
00:34:27.190 --> 00:34:28.817
♪ With just a napkin ♪

728
00:34:28.900 --> 00:34:29.985
♪ And ate him raw ♪

729
00:34:30.068 --> 00:34:32.112
♪ Did you hear about him? ♪

730
00:34:32.195 --> 00:34:33.738
♪ They made a statue ♪

731
00:34:33.822 --> 00:34:36.449
♪ I got it tattooed right on my arm ♪

732
00:34:36.533 --> 00:34:38.076
Right here.

733
00:34:38.159 --> 00:34:39.411
♪ Did you hear about ♪

734
00:34:39.494 --> 00:34:42.580
♪ I mean. no disrespect
but I straight up think you're lying ♪

735
00:34:42.664 --> 00:34:45.834
♪ Someone's overselling
and I'm not sure that I'm buying ♪

736
00:34:45.917 --> 00:34:47.168
♪ I've stopped a cyclone ♪

737
00:34:47.252 --> 00:34:49.087
♪ An avalanche and a tsunami ♪

738
00:34:49.170 --> 00:34:51.631
♪ I've tied a giant octopus's
arms like origami ♪

739
00:34:53.425 --> 00:34:54.968
♪ A criminal at heart ♪

740
00:34:55.051 --> 00:34:56.553
♪ Each job's a work of art ♪

741
00:34:56.636 --> 00:34:57.929
♪ You're swimming with a shark ♪

742
00:34:58.013 --> 00:35:00.098
♪ Check your pockets ♪

743
00:35:00.181 --> 00:35:03.143
♪ I've saved a thousand lives
including yours tonight ♪

744
00:35:03.226 --> 00:35:04.894
♪ No question I'm that guy ♪

745
00:35:04.978 --> 00:35:07.147
♪ Did you hear about him? ♪

746
00:35:07.230 --> 00:35:08.815
♪ He's a hero ♪

747
00:35:08.898 --> 00:35:11.526
♪ He's a leader He's the man ♪

748
00:35:11.610 --> 00:35:13.820
♪ Did you hear about her? ♪

749
00:35:13.903 --> 00:35:15.405
-♪ She's a savage ♪
-Watch out.

750
00:35:15.488 --> 00:35:18.241
♪ The type of bad witch
you don't ever want to cross ♪

751
00:35:18.325 --> 00:35:20.410
♪ Did you hear about him? ♪

752
00:35:20.493 --> 00:35:23.705
♪ I moved a mountain
I saved a castle ♪

753
00:35:23.788 --> 00:35:24.789
♪ With just my charm ♪

754
00:35:24.873 --> 00:35:26.916
♪ Did you hear about her? ♪

755
00:35:27.000 --> 00:35:30.211
♪ She ripped the wings off
of Tinkerbell. y'all ♪

756
00:35:30.295 --> 00:35:31.463
♪ What else you want? ♪

757
00:35:31.546 --> 00:35:34.466
Truth be told. Tinkerbell
can grow her wings back. Okay?

758
00:35:34.549 --> 00:35:36.051
Oh! That's good to know.

759
00:35:36.134 --> 00:35:37.677
Yeah.

760
00:35:37.761 --> 00:35:41.139
♪ Everywhere I go
A parade follows after ♪

761
00:35:41.222 --> 00:35:44.142
♪ He's putting on a show
while preventing a disaster ♪

762
00:35:44.225 --> 00:35:45.727
♪ I'm wiser. meaner. cooler ♪

763
00:35:45.810 --> 00:35:49.022
♪ And you can't get nothing past her ♪

764
00:35:49.105 --> 00:35:51.191
-♪ No. you can't ♪
-♪ Did you hear about ♪

765
00:36:16.549 --> 00:36:18.134
♪ Did you hear about ♪

766
00:36:18.218 --> 00:36:19.844
♪ Did you hear about ♪

767
00:36:19.928 --> 00:36:21.429
♪ Did you hear about ♪

768
00:36:22.972 --> 00:36:28.144
♪ Hey ♪

769
00:36:28.228 --> 00:36:30.563
♪ Did you hear about them? ♪

770
00:36:34.859 --> 00:36:37.529
♪ Did you hear about them ♪

771
00:36:38.571 --> 00:36:40.323
Whoo!

772
00:36:41.241 --> 00:36:42.992
They cheated. They had to have cheated.

773
00:36:43.076 --> 00:36:45.537
-That was good.
-Let's go!

774
00:36:45.620 --> 00:36:47.372
-Oh. I'm sorry.
-It's okay. bud.

775
00:36:47.455 --> 00:36:48.623
We'll get them next time.

776
00:36:48.707 --> 00:36:50.500
We can't argue that.

777
00:36:50.583 --> 00:36:51.668
VK's got it.

778
00:36:51.751 --> 00:36:53.044
A VK win?

779
00:36:53.128 --> 00:36:55.714
Did your sister forget
who kidnapped your mom?

780
00:36:55.797 --> 00:36:56.881
Are you kidding me?

781
00:36:58.341 --> 00:37:01.010
You're siding with them? With him?

782
00:37:03.263 --> 00:37:05.724
He could be in
on this with his dad. for all we know.

783
00:37:05.807 --> 00:37:07.767
Look. I may be the little sister.

784
00:37:07.851 --> 00:37:10.353
but at least I'm brave enough
to say what everyone's thinking.

785
00:37:10.437 --> 00:37:12.439
Okay. Hey.

786
00:37:12.522 --> 00:37:13.898
I think that's my cue.

787
00:37:16.526 --> 00:37:18.278
Pink. you shouldn't have said that.

788
00:37:20.405 --> 00:37:21.406
Max?

789
00:37:23.950 --> 00:37:25.326
Red. wait.

790
00:37:25.410 --> 00:37:27.328
Can we talk about this afternoon?

791
00:37:27.412 --> 00:37:29.789
And now this? I mean. siding with the VKs?

792
00:37:29.873 --> 00:37:32.375
I know. I'm used
to their way of doing things.

793
00:37:32.459 --> 00:37:33.918
Well. you kind of blew me off.

794
00:37:34.002 --> 00:37:36.045
I thought we were gonna
figure this out together.

795
00:37:36.129 --> 00:37:37.380
It's not like that. I'm just...

796
00:37:37.464 --> 00:37:39.466
You don't want to listen
to what I have to say.

797
00:37:39.549 --> 00:37:40.717
I'm not sure why I even came.

798
00:37:40.800 --> 00:37:44.512
I thought you came to help clean up
the mess we left in our wake. Chloe.

799
00:37:44.596 --> 00:37:45.597
Right now that's Max.

800
00:37:45.680 --> 00:37:46.806
He's trying to help. too.

801
00:37:46.890 --> 00:37:49.559
and he's being judged
for what his dad did. not for who he is.

802
00:37:50.268 --> 00:37:51.269
Sound familiar?

803
00:37:51.770 --> 00:37:53.021
Yeah.

804
00:37:53.104 --> 00:37:55.064
I'll go with you. It's my mess. too.

805
00:37:55.148 --> 00:37:57.108
No. I think he needs to hear it from me.

806
00:38:03.740 --> 00:38:07.952
For what it's worth. I'm still
investigating if Pink and I are related.

807
00:38:09.120 --> 00:38:12.081
She doesn't trust me.
It's kind of a common theme in my life.

808
00:38:15.919 --> 00:38:17.003
I trust you.

809
00:38:17.879 --> 00:38:20.215
You didn't
have to come here in the first place.

810
00:38:20.298 --> 00:38:25.512
And if we can save my mom.
maybe it's not too late to help your dad.

811
00:38:25.595 --> 00:38:27.096
Why would you want to do that?

812
00:38:28.097 --> 00:38:30.350
Because I still believe
there's good in him.

813
00:38:30.433 --> 00:38:33.645
Well. my whole life.
everyone else has said the opposite. so...

814
00:38:35.980 --> 00:38:37.482
I'm sorry. Max.

815
00:38:37.565 --> 00:38:38.650
It's his own fault.

816
00:38:39.317 --> 00:38:41.027
His complete obsession

817
00:38:41.110 --> 00:38:43.446
with finding this thing
he saw in high school.

818
00:38:43.530 --> 00:38:45.073
All he ever talked about.

819
00:38:45.156 --> 00:38:46.467
You don't understand. Max.

820
00:38:46.491 --> 00:38:48.910
I saw them. They traveled through time.

821
00:38:50.703 --> 00:38:52.372
Like time traveling is even a thing.

822
00:38:52.455 --> 00:38:53.581
Time travel?

823
00:38:54.374 --> 00:38:56.835
Yeah. that's why everyone
thinks he's a madman.

824
00:39:04.843 --> 00:39:05.927
I keep thinking

825
00:39:06.845 --> 00:39:10.932
if I could just get him
to bargain with us. but with what?

826
00:39:12.475 --> 00:39:14.060
Anything he can't live without?

827
00:39:32.745 --> 00:39:34.789
Oh. Sorry. I'll just...

828
00:39:34.873 --> 00:39:36.916
Not on my account.
I've got nothing to hide.

829
00:39:40.003 --> 00:39:41.087
Thanks.

830
00:39:42.130 --> 00:39:43.756
Just looking for a spot for the night.

831
00:39:43.840 --> 00:39:46.175
You and your fearless leader on the outs?

832
00:39:46.259 --> 00:39:48.511
Red's not my leader. She's my friend.

833
00:39:48.595 --> 00:39:49.846
-We're partners.
-Right.

834
00:39:49.929 --> 00:39:51.556
Like the Smees are mine.

835
00:39:51.639 --> 00:39:55.518
Look. Red's the alpha and you're... not.

836
00:39:55.602 --> 00:39:57.186
It's just nature. You can't change it.

837
00:39:57.270 --> 00:39:59.647
You'd be surprised what you can change.

838
00:40:00.982 --> 00:40:02.108
I don't know.

839
00:40:02.191 --> 00:40:05.945
I just keep thinking that if everything
and everyone can change...

840
00:40:08.865 --> 00:40:10.617
what are we supposed to hold on to?

841
00:40:11.451 --> 00:40:12.952
You know. people always say.

842
00:40:13.036 --> 00:40:15.872
"Oh. you poor thing.
Captain Hook as a father."

843
00:40:15.955 --> 00:40:17.999
But my dad. he always taught us

844
00:40:18.082 --> 00:40:19.751
you only have yourself to rely on.

845
00:40:20.293 --> 00:40:22.045
It's the best lesson I ever learned.

846
00:40:23.338 --> 00:40:24.631
It sounds lonely.

847
00:40:24.714 --> 00:40:25.798
Is that so?

848
00:40:28.468 --> 00:40:30.678
Well. I ain't never let me down yet.

849
00:40:31.304 --> 00:40:33.640
Can you say the same
about your partner Red?

850
00:40:38.227 --> 00:40:39.979
I'll find somewhere else to sleep tonight.

851
00:40:40.063 --> 00:40:41.439
Yeah. you do that.

852
00:40:43.274 --> 00:40:44.525
Hey. Princess.

853
00:40:46.361 --> 00:40:47.904
Be careful who you trust.

854
00:40:47.987 --> 00:40:49.656
-We made it!
-Felix?

855
00:40:49.739 --> 00:40:51.366
-We made it!
-Robbie!

856
00:40:53.701 --> 00:40:54.702
Ouch!

857
00:40:54.786 --> 00:40:56.704
Oh. Felix!

858
00:40:57.288 --> 00:40:58.790
